<subSubSection id="C330655BFFA5FF97FF5B8E152E7E1EE2" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8B9536D0FFA5FF97FF5B8E152C4B1D33" blockId="5.[136,370,1282,1309]" box="[136,370,1282,1309]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<heading id="D0DD81BCFFA5FF97FF5B8E152C4B1D33" bold="true" box="[136,370,1282,1309]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FF5B8E152C4B1D33" bold="true" box="[136,370,1282,1309]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FF5B8E152C3D1D32" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[136,260,1282,1309]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FF5B8E152C3D1D32" bold="true" box="[136,260,1282,1309]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Wendy’
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536D0FFA5FF97FF5B8E5C2E7E1EE2" blockId="5.[136,1452,1355,2066]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
By far most of the kalanchoes available in the horticultural trade today have been produced in continental Europe, the 
<collectingCountry id="F33D7640FFA5FF97FF618E782C4A1DA6" box="[178,371,1391,1417]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">United Kingdom</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry id="F33D7640FFA5FF97FE0A8E782F491DA6" box="[473,624,1391,1417]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">United States</collectingCountry>
where numerous hybrids and cultivars are offered for sale, especially for indoor cultivation, or for cultivation in greenhouses. One such cultivar, 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FC638E842EFA1D83" box="[944,963,1427,1452]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">K</emphasis>
. ‘Wendy’ (
<figureCitation id="13112A55FFA5FF97FB938E8429BD1D82" box="[1088,1156,1426,1453]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1549,1571]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,317,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-85@6.[151,1435,317,1524]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Material available in the horticultural trade under the name Kalanchoe ‘Wendy’ or, as we propose here, K. porphyrocalyx ‘Wendy’. Photograph: Ronen Shtein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413209/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), a single-flowered entity, was regarded by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA5FF97FE918EA02F0C1DFE" author="Springate, L. S." box="[322,565,1462,1489]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" pagination="178 - 185" refId="ref9004" refString="Springate, L. S. (1995) Crassulaceae. 3. Kalanchoe Adanson. In: Cullen, J., Alexander, J. C. M., Brady, A., Brickell, C. D., Green, P. S., Heywood, V. H., Jorgensen, P. - M., Jury, S. L., Knees, S. G., Leslie, A. C., Matthews, V. A., Robson, N. K. B., Walters, S. M., Wijnands, D. O. &amp; Yeo, P. F. (Eds.) The European Garden Flora. A manual for the identification of plants cultivated in Europe, both out-ofdoors and under glass. Vol. IV. Dicotyledons (Part II). Press Syndicate of the Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York and Melbourne, pp. 178 - 185." type="book chapter" year="1995">Springate (1995: 181)</bibRefCitation>
as having been derived from a hybrid between 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FBE88EA029891DFF" authorityName="Hilsenberg &amp; Bojer ex Tulasne" authorityYear="1857" box="[1083,1200,1463,1488]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="miniata">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FBE88EA029891DFF" box="[1083,1200,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">K. miniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FB308EA0289D1DFE" box="[1251,1444,1463,1489]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FB308EA0289D1DFE" box="[1251,1444,1463,1489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FF5B8ECC2C381DDA" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[136,257,1499,1525]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FF5B8ECC2C381DDA" box="[136,257,1499,1525]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Wendy’ was described as follows (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA5FF97FD4D8ECC2EB31DDA" author="Springate, L. S." box="[670,906,1498,1525]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" pagination="178 - 185" refId="ref9004" refString="Springate, L. S. (1995) Crassulaceae. 3. Kalanchoe Adanson. In: Cullen, J., Alexander, J. C. M., Brady, A., Brickell, C. D., Green, P. S., Heywood, V. H., Jorgensen, P. - M., Jury, S. L., Knees, S. G., Leslie, A. C., Matthews, V. A., Robson, N. K. B., Walters, S. M., Wijnands, D. O. &amp; Yeo, P. F. (Eds.) The European Garden Flora. A manual for the identification of plants cultivated in Europe, both out-ofdoors and under glass. Vol. IV. Dicotyledons (Part II). Press Syndicate of the Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York and Melbourne, pp. 178 - 185." type="book chapter" year="1995">Springate 1995: 181</bibRefCitation>
): “Shrublet to 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FBE18ECC29451DDA" box="[1074,1148,1499,1525]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="cm" value="40.0">40 cm</quantity>
, semi-erect, with very few fine simple hairs only in the inflorescences. Stems soon thickening and epidermis separating into plates. Leaves ovate to oblong-lanceolate with uneven, shallow, rounded teeth, 4–7 × 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FCBA8D352EEF1E12" box="[873,982,1570,1597]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="cm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.0">1–2.5 cm</quantity>
, tapered at base; stalk indistinct. Stem of inflorescence usually 3-branched from base with 15–30 pendent flowers. Corolla urn-shaped, tube rose-purple, ca. 2.3 × 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FF1A8D7C2C231EAA" box="[201,282,1643,1669]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="cm" value="1.3">1.3 cm</quantity>
; lobes ovate, yellow, 5 × 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FDEF8D7C2F431EAA" box="[572,634,1643,1669]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="6.0">6mm</quantity>
. Anthers and styles just projecting from corolla-tube; filaments fused to corolla for 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FED78D982C291E87" box="[260,272,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">c</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FECC8D992C621E86" box="[287,347,1678,1705]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="5.0">5mm</quantity>
. Similar to 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FE0F8D982CD61E87" box="[476,495,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">K</emphasis>
. [
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FDD58D982F461E86" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[518,639,1679,1705]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FDD58D982F461E86" box="[518,639,1679,1705]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FD438D982E0B1E86" box="[656,818,1679,1705]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FD438D982E0B1E86" box="[656,818,1679,1705]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but coarser and more floriferous when grown in similar conditions. Sometimes self-fertilised, seedlings very variable.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C330655BFFA5FF94FF6E8DC02E64190B" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="231" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9536D0FFA5FF94FF6E8DC02E64190B" blockId="5.[136,1452,1355,2066]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1451,158,293]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="231" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA5FF97FF6E8DC02C851EDE" author="Springate, L. S." box="[189,444,1750,1777]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" pagination="178 - 185" refId="ref9004" refString="Springate, L. S. (1995) Crassulaceae. 3. Kalanchoe Adanson. In: Cullen, J., Alexander, J. C. M., Brady, A., Brickell, C. D., Green, P. S., Heywood, V. H., Jorgensen, P. - M., Jury, S. L., Knees, S. G., Leslie, A. C., Matthews, V. A., Robson, N. K. B., Walters, S. M., Wijnands, D. O. &amp; Yeo, P. F. (Eds.) The European Garden Flora. A manual for the identification of plants cultivated in Europe, both out-ofdoors and under glass. Vol. IV. Dicotyledons (Part II). Press Syndicate of the Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York and Melbourne, pp. 178 - 185." type="book chapter" year="1995">Springate (1995: 181)</bibRefCitation>
does not mention the occurrence of double flowers in this cultivar, and twelve years later confirmed that the only double flowers in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FD758DEC2E011F3A" box="[678,824,1787,1813]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Crassulaceae</taxonomicName>
that he was aware of was in the CALANDIVA® series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FF5B8C082C381F16" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[136,257,1823,1849]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FF5B8C082C381F16" box="[136,257,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in a plant of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FE168C0829951F16" authority="(Linnaeus 1753: 430) Holub (1978: 144)" authorityName="Holub" authorityPageNumber="144" authorityYear="1978" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="430" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[453,1196,1822,1849]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Hylotelephium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maximum">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FE168C082FE71F17" box="[453,734,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Hylotelephium maximum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA5FF97FD3F8C082EF71F16" author="Linnaeus, C." box="[748,974,1822,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" refId="ref8470" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species plantarum, exhibentes plantas rite cognitas, ad generarelatas, cum differentiis specificis, nominibus trivialibus, synonymis selectis, locis natalibus, secundum systema sexuale digestas. Vol. 1. Salvius, Stockholm, 560 pp. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 669" type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus 1753: 430</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA5FF97FC0F8C0829951F16" author="Holub, J." box="[988,1196,1823,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" pagination="144" refId="ref8121" refString="Holub, J. (1978) Hylotelephium maximum (L.) Holub. Severoceskou Prirodou; Sbornik Severoceske Pobocky Ceskoslovenske Botanike Spolecnosti. Litomerice 8 - 9 (2): 144." type="journal article" year="1978">Holub (1978: 144)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
that he encountered in 
<collectingCountry id="F33D7640FFA5FF97FF5B8C542DD31F72" box="[136,234,1859,1885]" name="Hungary" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Hungary</collectingCountry>
(Springate 2007: 95). 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FE368C542F671F72" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[485,606,1859,1885]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FE368C542F671F72" box="[485,606,1859,1885]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Wendy’, as illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA5FF97FC578C5429531F72" author="Brickell, C." box="[900,1130,1858,1885]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" refId="ref7416" refString="Brickell, C. (Editor-in-Chief) (2003) The Royal Horticultural Society A - Z encyclopedia of garden plants. Vol. 2. K - Z. Revised edition. Dorling Kindersley, London, pp. 593 - 1128." type="book" year="2003">Brickell (2003: 594)</bibRefCitation>
, and also at https://www.rhs. org.uk/Plants/66915/i-Kalanchoe-i-Wendy/Details, appears to be very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA5FF97FBC48C7029E21FAE" box="[1047,1243,1895,1921]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FBC48C7029E21FAE" box="[1047,1243,1895,1921]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species. Both 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA5FF97FF5B8C9C2C531F8A" author="Brickell, C." box="[136,362,1930,1957]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" refId="ref7383" refString="Brickell, C. (Editor-in-Chief) (1998) The Royal Horticultural Society A - Z encyclopedia of garden plants. Corrected reprint. Dorling Kindersley, London, 1080 pp." type="book" year="1998">Brickell (1998: 578)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA5FF97FE4D8C9C2FB81F8A" author="Brickell, C." box="[414,641,1930,1957]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" refId="ref7416" refString="Brickell, C. (Editor-in-Chief) (2003) The Royal Horticultural Society A - Z encyclopedia of garden plants. Vol. 2. K - Z. Revised edition. Dorling Kindersley, London, pp. 593 - 1128." type="book" year="2003">Brickell (2003: 594)</bibRefCitation>
describe 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA5FF97FD3A8C9C2E3D1F8B" box="[745,772,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">K.</emphasis>
‘Wendy’ as: “Pendent to semi-erect, perennial succulent with ovate to oblong-ovate, slightly scalloped, glossy, mid-green leaves, to 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FC758CB82EEF1FE6" box="[934,982,1967,1993]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="cm" value="7.0">7cm</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FC348CB829351FE5" box="[999,1036,1967,1994]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="in" value="3.0">3in</quantity>
) long. Corymb-like panicles of bellshaped, orange- to yellow-tipped, purple-red flowers. 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FD0E8CC42E341FC2" box="[733,781,2003,2029]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="cm" value="3.0">3cm</quantity>
(1¼in) long are borne in late winter and early spring. Height and spread 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FED98CE02C71103E" box="[266,328,2039,2065]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="cm" value="30.0">30cm</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA5FF97FE8B8CE02CB5103D" box="[344,396,2039,2066]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.048" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="in" value="12.0">12in</quantity>
) (min. 10°C/50°F). Frost tender: plant may be damaged by temperatures below 5°C (41°F)”. Both works include an image of 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FE268B882F311897" box="[501,520,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">K</emphasis>
. ‘Wendy’ in flower. Note though that this description coincides closely with that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA6FF94FF5B8BD42C7318F3" box="[136,330,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FF5B8BD42C7318F3" box="[136,330,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species. In this hybrid, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA6FF94FD538BD42E7B18F3" box="[640,834,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FD538BD42E7B18F3" box="[640,834,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly overshadowed the contribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA6FF94FACB8BD428B718F3" authorityName="Hilsenberg &amp; Bojer ex Tulasne" authorityYear="1857" box="[1304,1422,195,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="miniata">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FACB8BD428B718F3" box="[1304,1422,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">K. miniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, if indeed it is of hybrid origin (see for example 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA6FF94FDAC8BF12930192F" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Allorge-Boiteau, L." box="[639,1033,230,257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" refId="ref7208" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Allorge-Boiteau, L. (1995) Kalanchoe (Crassulacees) de Madagascar. Systematique, ecophysiologie et phytochimie. ICSN, CNRS, 91198 Gif-sur-Yvette, Editions Karthala, Paris, 252 pp." type="book" year="1995">Boiteau &amp; Allorge-Boiteau 1995: 9</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA6FF94FBCD8BF129AE192F" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[1054,1175,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FBCD8BF129AE192F" box="[1054,1175,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Wendy’ was previously awarded a Royal Horticultural Society’s Award of Garden Merit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF556658FFA6FF94FF5B8D1A2CD51E68" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413209" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5413209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413209/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" startId="6.[136,229,1549,1571]" targetBox="[151,1435,317,1524]" targetPageId="6">
