<subSubSection id="C330655BFFA6FF94FF6E8D622C021F6B" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9536D0FFA6FF94FF6E8D622C021F6B" blockId="6.[136,1452,1653,1860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA6FF94FF6E8D622CDB1EA0" box="[189,482,1653,1679]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FF6E8D622CDB1EA0" box="[189,482,1653,1679]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Kalanchoe porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and any cultivars based on it, or derived from a hybrid of which this species is one parent, are not mentioned by major horticultural works such as 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA6FF94FC968D8E29961E9B" author="Bailey, L. H. &amp; Bailey, E. Z." box="[837,1199,1689,1716]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" refId="ref6575" refString="Bailey, L. H. &amp; Bailey, E. Z. (1976) Hortus Third. A concise dictionary of plants cultivated in the United States and Canada. Revised and expanded by The Staff of the Liberty Hyde Bailey Hortorium, Cornell University. Macmillan Publishing Company New York, and Collier Macmillan Publishers, London, 1290 pp." type="book" year="1976">Bailey &amp; Bailey (1976: 620–62)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA6FF94FB698D8E28911E9C" author="Graf, A. B." box="[1210,1448,1689,1716]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" refId="ref7908" refString="Graf, A. B. (1980 [January]) Exotica series 3. Pictorial cyclopedia of exotic plants from tropical regions. [12,000 illustrations, 204 plants in colour, guide to care of plants indoors, horticultural colour guide, plant geography]. 10 th edition. Roehrs Company Inc., E. Rutherford, N. J. 07073, USA, 1834 pp." type="book" year="1980">Graf (1980: 682–689</bibRefCitation>
, 1637–1638), and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA6FF94FE808DA92F891EF7" author="Bryant, G. &amp; Bryant, K. &amp; Rutherford, B. &amp; Vogan, R." box="[339,688,1725,1752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" refId="ref7587" refString="Bryant, G., Bryant, K., Rutherford, B. &amp; Vogan, R. (2005) Cacti &amp; Succulents. Kalanchoe. In: Barnard, L., Edwards, A., Etherington, K., Imwold, D., King, E., Malone, M. &amp; Parker, J. (Eds.) The ultimate plant book. New Holland, London, 1024 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Bryant 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FE7A8DA92CE41EF8" box="[425,477,1725,1751]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. (2005: 740–741)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B21FFA6FF94FD6E8DAA2E801EF7" author="Springate, L. S." box="[701,953,1725,1752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" pagination="178 - 185" refId="ref9004" refString="Springate, L. S. (1995) Crassulaceae. 3. Kalanchoe Adanson. In: Cullen, J., Alexander, J. C. M., Brady, A., Brickell, C. D., Green, P. S., Heywood, V. H., Jorgensen, P. - M., Jury, S. L., Knees, S. G., Leslie, A. C., Matthews, V. A., Robson, N. K. B., Walters, S. M., Wijnands, D. O. &amp; Yeo, P. F. (Eds.) The European Garden Flora. A manual for the identification of plants cultivated in Europe, both out-ofdoors and under glass. Vol. IV. Dicotyledons (Part II). Press Syndicate of the Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York and Melbourne, pp. 178 - 185." type="book chapter" year="1995">Springate (1995: 181)</bibRefCitation>
cites an illustration of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA6FF94FB1A8DAA287B1EF8" authorityName=", Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[1225,1346,1725,1751]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FB1A8DAA287B1EF8" box="[1225,1346,1725,1751]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Wendy’ that appeared in “Brickell, RHS gardeners’ encyclopedia of plants &amp; flowers, [p.] 384 (1989)”, and the cultivar name was established there for the first time, including direct reference to it being of hybrid origin (
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA6FF94FB298C11284B1F30" authorityName="Hilsenberg &amp; Bojer ex Tulasne" authorityYear="1857" box="[1274,1394,1798,1823]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="miniata">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FB298C11284B1F30" box="[1274,1394,1798,1823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">K. miniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
× 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D53FFA6FF94FA418C112C131F6C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA6FF94FA418C112C131F6C" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
